news.title: Plea in Delhi HC challenges clause of regulations for development of privately owned lands
news.para: The petitioner further said that the clause is in the nature of putting a restraint on the overall development of Delhi as it denies the regularisation of the existing structure on the privately-owned un-acquired land despite being in accordance with Unified Building Bye-Laws and Master Plan of Delhi.

news.title: SC verdict on Supertech's plea against demolition order of twin towers on Aug 31
news.para: On August 4, the top court had reserved its verdict on the batch of pleas while reprimanding NOIDA authority saying it is reeking with corruption and had connived with the builder over not providing the sanctioned plan to the homebuyers of Supertech's Emerald Court project.

news.title: Dubai developer Limitless set to agree third debt restructuring deal
news.para: It plans to enter into a lock-up agreement - a precursor to a long form term sheet and definitive documentation - with an ad-hoc group of creditors by the end of this month and with remaining creditors by the end of September to restructure the debt, an overview of the plan seen by Reuters showed.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board meet on need-based changes on September 8
news.para: Sources said the needbased changes matter will be discussed by keeping aspects like structural strength of houses, legal issues, and encroachments in mind. Officers will also share the current status.

news.title: Goa to seek one more month to ready coastal zone management plan
news.para: The state received 8,000 suggestions and objections on the CZMP from citizens during the July 8 public hearing. Different government agencies are working to verify these inputs.

news.title: Parsvnath Realcon starts construction of its stalled project in Delhi
news.para: Parsvnath Paramount consists of five towers including one separate Tower of EWS, having total 87 residential units in four towers and 45 units in EWS Tower.

news.title: East Delhi civic body rolls back proposal to increase property tax for shops
news.para: The committee in its report had suggested changing the category of such markets from D to A, which meant the unit area value would have increased from Rs 320 per square metre to 630 per sqm.

news.title: NGT issues notice to centre on plea challenging EC for high-rise near Delhi University
news.para: ​A bench headed by NGT Chairperson Justice Adarsh Kumar Goel issued notice to the Ministry of Environment and Forests, Young Builders Private Limited and others, seeking their responses within a month.

news.title: Delhi: NGT panel imposes Rs 96 lakh cost on building owner, tenants over violations
news.para: The building was missing a number of permissions and was operating multiple small factories and packaging units inside, when a fire broke out in February this year.

news.title: Maharashtra may clear changes in Mann-Mhalunge town planning scheme
news.para: The scheme which has been stuck for the last four years may gain momentum once the government approves the proposal, PMRDA officials said.

news.title: Morbi: Ceramic tiles to get costlier as production cost increases
news.para: "The prices of vitrified tiles have been raised by Rs 2 per square foot, which translates into an increase of 10-12%," said Mukesh Kundariya, president, vitrified tiles division, Morbi Ceramic Association (MCA).

news.title: Mangaluru civic body to hold demo on online property tax payment system
news.para: The city corporation will be able to launch the online Self-assessment system (SAS) property tax payment system soon after rectifying all initial issues, the commissioner said.

news.title: Unfair to say PVC prices are too high: Prakash Chhabria, Executive Chairman, Finolex
news.para: Chhabria did not agree that the rise in prices of PVC over the past year has been excessive, particularly as its prices have fluctuated drastically over the past few years.

news.title: Owners protest against Noida authority over five year delay in plot handover
news.para: While no official comment was available from the Noida Authority over the issue, its officials hinted at the "possibility of starting demarcation" of the plots from the beginning of next year.

news.title: Gurugram: BPTP Park Serene residents protest over incomplete work
news.para: They alleged that the developer took occupancy certificate (OC) for project in 2017 but failed to complete the pending work even after 4 years despite repeated complaints.
